Package Person

Class TravelAgent

java.lang.Object
Person.Person
Person.TravelAgent
public class TravelAgent extends Person
The TravelAgent class represents a travel agent in the cruise booking system.

This class extends the Person class and provides additional functionality specific to travel agents, such as account creation.

Key features of the TravelAgent class include:

  • Account creation for travel agents using the createAccount method.

  • Method Details

    • createAccount

      public boolean createAccount()
      Creates a new account with generic details for a Travel Agent.

      This method is a convenience method that invokes the createGenericAccount method with the account type set to "TRAVELAGENT". It creates a new Travel Agent account entry in the 'LOGINDATA' table with default details.

      Returns:
      true if the Travel Agent account is successfully created, false otherwise.
      See Also:
      • Person.createGenericAccount(String)

    • modifyTravelAgentAccount

      public static boolean modifyTravelAgentAccount(String currentUsername, String newUsername, String newPassword, String newAddress)
      Modifies the details of a Travel Agent account in the 'LOGINDATA' table.

      This method connects to the 'cruiseDatabase' using JDBC and performs the following steps:

      1. Updates the 'LOGINDATA' table with the provided new username, new password, and new address for the Travel Agent account identified by the current username.
      2. Returns true if the account details are successfully modified, false otherwise.
      Parameters:
      currentUsername - the current username of the Travel Agent account to be modified.
      newUsername - the new username for the Travel Agent account.
      newPassword - the new password for the Travel Agent account.
      newAddress - the new address for the Travel Agent account.
      Returns:
      true if the account details are successfully modified, false otherwise.
